Rebatho Madiba is the managing executive for business development at BCX. She took up the role in July 2022, after serving as executive of specialised sales for digital EXA at the group, where she was responsible for driving the sales of customer-centric and digital-focused solutions for BCX. Madiba previously worked as the SAP competency manager for Debswana, where she established the Debswana SAP Change and Training Management programme across its mines. She also worked at Transnet in various managerial positions, including as the general manager for IT operations. In this conference session, Madiba meets with Michael Avery to discuss the latest technologies and innovations in the financial services sector. Madiba unpacks these technologies and explains why it is important for financial services businesses to embrace them. She talks about BCX’s various solutions for the financial services sector and explains how they leverage the latest technologies to help businesses. Madiba also explains how BCX helps implement these important technologies without compromising business continuity. The full conference session between Michael Avery and BCX executive Rebatho Madiba is embedded below. 